U.S. Attacks on two Iranian oil platformsin the Gulf -- both of which were still blazing -- causeddamage estimated at 500 mln dlrs, Tehran Radio quoted IranianOil Minister Gholamreza Aqazadeh as saying.    The rigs, one of which was heavily shelled by four Americandestroyers on Monday, were still burning almost 24 hours afterthe attack and could cause widespread pollution in the Gulf,the minister told a news conference in Tehran. He said theReshadat rigs, 120 miles (200 km) east of Bahrain ininternational waters, were in the final stages ofreconstruction after an attack by Iraqi jets last year. REUTER&#3;